OL,3,CInfected blood scandal: What was it -
OL,4,Cand who was affected?
OL,6,FThe first group are people with
OL,7,Fhaemophilia - experts believe 1,250
OL,8,Fpeople contracted HIV and Hepatitis C.
OL,10,FTwo thirds then died of AIDS related
OL,11,Fillnesses, with an unknown amount
OL,12,Ftransferring HIV to their partners.
OL,14,FThe second group were those given
OL,15,Fblood transfusions after childbirth or
OL,16,Fsurgery - 27,000 of whom were infected
OL,17,Fwith Hepatitis C.
