OL,3,CInfected blood scandal: What was it -
OL,4,Cand who was affected?
OL,6,FThose who have campaigned for justice
OL,7,Fover the scandal include not only
OL,8,Fvictims themselves, but also their
OL,9,Ffamilies - many of whom had their
OL,10,Flives ruined because of the deaths of
OL,11,Ftheir parents.
OL,13,FIn total, more than 3,000 people are
OL,14,Fknown to have died. The Haemophilia
OL,15,FSociety also estimates that between
OL,16,Fthe start of the inquiry and the
OL,17,Fpublishing of its findings, another
OL,18,F650 will have also passed away.
